ARENA WARGAMES WARGAME JOIN SHOOT

   The Arena is the home of the Wargames. To play a game, just type 
"wargame" to see the current game's status, if any, and if there isn't 
one running, type "wargame start". You'll notice you have other options, 
as well, namely, teams, ammo, and hits.  These are all pretty much self 
explanatory. Simply type "wargame ammo #" to change the amount of 
ammunition a player has, "wargame hits #" to change the amount of hits a 
player can sustain before being eliminated, and "wargame teams #" for 
however many teams you might like. (0 is the default, and should be used 
for a free-for-all type game) When a game begins, type "join" and you 
will be transported to the Arena. Once all the players have joined, the 
gamesmaster should type "wargame run". Once the game begins, an exit will 
appear. You may shoot your opponent from up to three rooms away, but, as 
the distance increases, your accuracy will suffer. You only have a 
limited number of shots, so use them carefully. 

   To attempt to hit a player, use the command "shoot <player>". If he is 
in a room west of you, for example, the command "shoot <player> w" will 
allow you to snipe him. However, if you miss him, he will be alerted to 
your presence. 

   You will be eliminated after being hit twice, and will be transported 
back to the temple of Midgaard. If both players use up all shots, the 
match goes into sudden death, and each player has 99 shots. Level does 
not matter, immortals and newbies can play alike, although some skills 
will be beneficial, such as sneak, hide, and scout. Immortals of course, 
are forbidden to use potentially useful commands not available to 
mortals. The results of the match, as well as events such as a player 
getting wounded, are broadcast throughout the arena zone. 

   A spectators room is available for those who wish to yell encouragement,
taunts, and the like, as well as keep abreast of current wargame happenings. 
This room, which contains an arena board, is up and south from the Temple 
of Midgaard. 

   Enjoy! 
