BOARD

A board is where you can post a message for everyone to read. Most boards
are in the librare, but there are also some boards by the guilds and in
the clanhouses.

> read board
> read #
> write <headline>
> remove #

See Also: WRITE, MIDGAARD
#
BOT

A BOT is a player who uses a script to cast beneficial spells on 
other (less fortunate) people. Bots may be public (in which case
they are often located 2u from the temple) or may be limited to
certain clans, groups or individuals.

NOTE: If you are Botting, you MAY NOT do so unattended. Immortals
may check bots at any time, and if a timely response is not
forthcoming, they may be jailed.

#
BRIEF

When in brief mode, you don't see the descriptions of the room you are 
in; only the name of the room and the people and objects there.  Unless 
you're very familiar with the area in which you're travelling, however, 
it is not advisable to use this command.  Frequently, you will find small 
but vital hints in the descriptions of the rooms: An extra peek at your 
surroundings could mean the difference between life and death!

> TOGGLE BRIEF

See also: TOGGLE COMPACT
#
BUILDER BUILDERS BUILDING

So you'd like to be a builder at Elite?  First you need an idea;
something interesting, exciting, unique, and well-planned.  Then you'll
have to follow through with that idea and turn it into reality.  We'd
like to have some of the most creative and original areas here at Elite,
and we'll need your help to do that.  Becoming a builder can be quite
rewarding, it's a great feeling to have people running through your
latest creation, wondering how someone could be insane enough to write
such a unique area!

Please note that building does not require #rany#N coding experience!

It's quite easy to learn, and we have a wide range of help files and
tools available to anyone who'd like to give it a shot.  Don't be
discourage if you've never built before.  Some of our best areas have
been created by first-time builders.

The first step you'll need to take on your way to becoming a builder is
submitting an area proposal.  This can be one of the most difficult
steps in a sometimes very long process.  You'll need to mail the
following information to #gGlob#N. (email or mudmail)

    1) The proposed name for your area
    2) Approximate number of rooms needed
    3) A description of the theme (or story) behind the area
    4) A sample room description
    5) A sample mob description
    6) A sample object description
    7) Any additional information that might be useful for helping to
       visualize your area
    
Your proposal will be reviewed by the current builders, and you should
receive a reply within 2 weeks from initial submission.  Don't be
discouraged if your original proposal is not accepted, with work that
idea could eventually turn into reality.

Once your proposal is accepted, you will receive a zone number (or
numbers if necessary) so you may begin work.  You will be allowed a
reasonable amount of time to build your area.  In cases where an area is
taking an unusually long time to be built, you may be contacted.
Because we are currently limited by the number of available zones, your
zone numbers may be reassigned if you do not respond.

Be aware that there are a few things that must be done before your area
is implemented:

    1) The area must be free of all grammar and spelling errors.
    2) The area must be playtested.
    3) All mobs and objects must be approved by the appropriate groups.
    4) A formal walkthrough must be completed.
    5) A map must be submitted (in text or image format).

If you have any questions regarding building, the best way to get
answers is to either contact one of the members of the World Group
(check the immlist for some names) or email Glob.
Additional building information can be found at 
"#Chttp://hemsidor.torget.se/users/e/Egba/BuildDoc/index.html#N"
#
