"CLAN RANKS"

Each clan has ranks within it.  There are 10 ranks in each clan.  The
ranking decides what you can do and what responsibilities you have.   
This is a sample standard ranking:

        Applying
        New member
        Member
        Soldier
        Adept
        Advisor
        Counselor
        Ruler
        Queen
        Deity

They may have different names though, depending on the clan.

#
"CLAN PROBATION"

After being approved to form a clan, the newly formed clan will be 
put on one month's probation.  In this time the clan will be reviewed 
by the #CClan Group#N.  The rest is subjective.  Some of the subjective 
items could include *but are not limited to*:  organization, leadership, 
interclan relations, activity.  Also, current clans will be reviewed 
as needed.  Any clan which does not show improvement while on probation 
will be deleted.

#
"CLAN MOB"

The Clan Group is proud to announce a new addition to the list of 
ways your clan can spend, spend, spend here on Elite.  

  #CRestrictions#N

1. Mobs must be level 109 (immune to summon, charm)
2. Mobs must be sentinel.
3. Mobs will have stats comparable with guildmasters and other 
   shopkeepers
4. Mobs will have 0 exp assigned.
5. Mobs may be shopkeepers such as bartenders (Shopkeepers
   come with a free LAWFUL flag)
6. Mobs can not buy items
7. Mobs can not use the public channels
8. Mob actions can not be offensive.

Clans can buy a maximum of one (1) shopkeeper and three (3) other 
(non-shopkeeper) mobs.  No clan will be allowed more than a total of 
four (4) clan mobs.

  #CShopkeeper Standards#N

Shopkeepers for clans may not sell items at prices that are below 
the going price in town.  If bread is 10 gold at the Baker, clan 
shopkeepers can also sell bread for 10 gold.  Shopkeepers can not 
sell equipment of any kind.

They can sell a maximum of ten (10) items.  These may include 
original food or drink items, or potions, wands or scrolls sold 
in other shops around the Mud. All items are flagged for the 
particular clans use only.


  #CRequesting Clan Mobs#N

All requests should be sent to the Clan Group for review.  Once 
everything is approved, the mobs will be added to your clan's files, 
tested and put in for the next reboot.

   The following should be sent with your request:
        1. Mob decriptions
        2. Actions (for mobs with actions)
        3. List of items sold and prices (for shopkeepers)
        4. Room the mob will load into
#
"CLAN SHOPKEEPER" "CLAN EQ"
This should not be confused with the shopkeeper in your clanhouse
selling potions, food and scrolls. The Clan Shopkeeper lives next
to the Clan Board in the Midgaard Library (swwnnnnne).

Clans may have up to 3 special clan items, which will be identical
in function to an existing piece of non-quest equipment. Members
of that clan will be able to EXCHANGE one of the regular items, for
its Clan Equivalent. The Exchange is free, but there is a one-off 
cost of 50 million to create the special clan item.

Example: Minions of Mokky create a Spider Shield, which is an
exact copy of a Large Round Shield, for 50mil. Any member of
Minions of Mokky can take a Large Round Shield to the Clan
Shopkeeper, and exchange it for a Spider Shield, which only other
members of their clan can use.

How to use: Go to the Clan Equipment Shopkeeper in the Library
and type "list". This shows a list of all your clans available
equipment, and the item you need to bring to exchange for it.
Drop the item on the ground, and type "exchange ##" where ## 
is the number of the exchange you want to make.

