CLERIC
Clerics have an ancient belief in not carrying sharp weapons. Hence,
they can only wield bludgeoning weapons. This class gives you the wisdom
of peace, and the magics of blessing and healing, though it is possible
to advance to utilise more violent spells.

    You can improve your spells and skills by using the practice
command in Cleric Guild.

See also: PRACTICE, GUILD, MIDGAARD

#
"CHARM PERSON"
Usage         : cast 'charm person' <victim> : cast 7 <victim>
Cost          : 45 Mn
Duration      : 10 Hours
Save          : Save vs. Magic

When cast, this spell will cause the target to follow the caster, and
complete any task ordered of him by his master. This ONLY works with
mobs though. :)

To succed with this spell, you need to be higher level than the mob.
#
"CHILL TOUCH"

Usage           : cast 'chill touch' <victim> : cast 8 <victim>
Damage          : 1d6 + level/2 (max 20)
Cost            : 11 Mn
Duration        : instant for damage, see below for affections.

Chill Touch has a victim affect of -1 strength for 4 hours, if the saving
throw is not successful.  If the saving throw is successful, the 
affection is -1 strength for 1 hour.
#
CHOP

A general skill.  The knowledge of how to use chopping weapons like 
different sorts of axes.  You will have a greater chance of hitting your 
enemy with a chopping weapon.

See also: PIERCE BLUDGEON SLASH STAB
#
"CIRCLE AROUND"

This rogue skill is like backstab.  If the heat of a fight, you can try 
to nimbly circle around your enemy's defenses and put your dagger in it's 
neck.

> circle
