DIAGNOSE

diagnose
diagnose <character>

The DIAGNOSE command tells you how wounded a character looks.  If you are
fighting someone, you can use DIAGNOSE with no arguments to diagnose the
person you're fighting.

> diagnose
> diagnose rasmussen

See Also: LOOK
#
DISARM

This skill allows you to try to disarm your opponent.
#
"DISPEL EVIL"
Usage           : cast 'dispel evil' <victim> : cast 22 <victim>
Damage          : 6d8 + 6 to evil characters (see below)
Cost            : 30 Mn
Duration        : instant

   This spell, when cast, will do damage to the victim if and only if the
victim is evil and the caster is non evil. If the caster is evil, only
the caster will receive damage.
#
DISPLAY

Display format is: display [H|M|V|norm|all||none|vt|ansi]
disp h      - display hp
disp m      - display mana
disp v      - display movement
disp norm   - will reset to a prompt displaying Hp Mn Mv
disp all    - display Hp/Mn/Mv/Victim-status
          (format on your screen will be 100h | 102m | 97v > for example)
disp vt     - vt100 term emulation(status will be at bottom of screen)
disp ansi   - ansi terminal emulation

See also RESIZE REDRAW
#
DODGE

A thief skill that makes you able to dodge your enemy's attacks.  The 
better you are the more attacks you can dodge.
#
DONATE

This command takes an object that you no longer want and deposits it in 
the donation room of Midgaard to assist newbies in getting started.  
There is a 75% chance objects donated will wind up in a donation room in 
Midgaard, and a 25% chance the item will be junked.

donate <object>
donate <number> coins

> donate shield
> donate all.bread
> donate 500 coins

See also: SACRIFICE DROP
#
DRACONIAN

Draconians are the descendants of an ancient group of cursed dragons.
They were created from the offspring of these dragons to serve the forces
of evil, and most still do to this day.  They have the strength of
their dragon ancestors, and many have their intelligence, but because
each line of draconians evolved from a different kind of dragon there
is much variation.  Draconians are similar in appearance to lizardmen,
but they tend to have shorter tails or no tails at all.  They are
capable of speech, but they share the tell-tale hiss of lizardmen.
Draconians do not like to be compared to their lizardman cousins,
believing that they are far superior to them in all ways.  They dislike
humans end elves but has been known to associate with some of the more
evil races.
#
DRAGON
The Dragon race on Elite is a race so powerful, that one must endure
a long and intense quest to attain it.  Dragons are strong fighters and
magic users that, although are not very dexterous, have incredible
strength and vitality.  It is said that they possess natural properties
of armor in their extremely tough scales.  They also have the rare 
ability to fly without the aid of magic.  

#
"DRAGON BREATH"
Usage           : cast 'dragon breath' : cast 103
Damage          : (1d20 + 10) * (level / 5)
                  to all opponents in room.
Cost            : 80 Mn
Duration        : instant
