DROP

If you lose interest in a carried item, you can drop it on the ground.

drop <item>
drop all.<item>
drop all
drop <number> coins

> drop bottle
> drop all.bread
> drop all
> drop 1000 coins

See also: GET SACRIFICE DONATE
#
DROW DARKELF

The drow are an evil race of subterranean creatures that are closely
related to elves.  They are cruel and cunning, preferring the darkness of
dark smoky rooms to the sunny squares of Midgaard.  Drows are usually
shorter than elves, and have much less variation in coloring.  Most drows
have dark hair and dark eyes to match their dark souls.  Their eyesight
has evolved tremendously in their time under the surface to be perfect
for walking around caverns and caves without a light source, but they 
tend to have trouble on the surface because of the relative brightness.  
Drows are not well-liked by other races, but they don't seem to mind much 
since the feeling is mutual.
#
DRUID

Druids live in harmony with their prime deity - mother earth.  These
priests have an innate knowledege of the forest and the natural magics
of healing.

    You can improve your spells and skills by using the practice
command in Cleric Guild.

See also: PRACTICE, GUILD, MIDGAARD

#
DUAL-CLASS DUAL

When you are adept in your class, why not try a new trade?
#
"DUAL WEAPONS"

This thief skill lets you attack with a second weapon held in your hand,
but you can only attack with it once per round.
#
DUCK

These creatures are about the same size as a halfling, but have a duck's 
head. They are often sailors.  Though they speak common, their beaks 
makes it sound awkward.  They should however always be considered armed 
and dangerous.
#
DWARF

Dwarves are a short and stocky race with strong arms and a will to match.
Dwarven men have long beards while the women have short beards.  Both
sexes normally have earth-colored skin and dark hair, though some dwarves
have been found with fairer coloring.  The dwarves that live in Midgaard
are mostly descendants of the mining dwarves from the mountains in the
east, and share with them the ability to see well in the darkness of the
caves and caverns.  Dwarves are fond of food and fight, and will indulge
in both if allowed.  Their stubbornness often frustrates other races, but
makes them wonderful comrades-in-arms.
#
"EARTHQUAKE"
Usage           : cast 'earthquake' : cast 23
Damage          : 2d8 + level/4 (max of 30)  TO all opponents in room
Cost            : 20 Mn
Duration        : instant
