"ELEMENTAL CANNON"
Usage           : cast 'elemental cannon' <victim> : cast 105 <victim>
Damage          : (1d20 + 30) * (level / 5)
Cost            : 75 Mn
Duration        : instant
#
ELF

Elves are slender creatures with pointed ears and graceful features.  
Elven folk vary in coloration depending on their region of origin.  They 
can be dark or fair or even blue-green with hair and eyes to match.  They 
are an ancient race and consider themselves to be superior to all others
because they believe that they were the first intelligent race of beings.
Elves are long-lived and intelligent.  They are very interested in magic,
and because of their long lives often become quite proficient at it.
Elves tend to avoid their larger cousins, the humans, and try to avoid
fighting when possible.  They prefer to use brain more than brawn, and
are often quite successful at turning a foe away without even raising
a sword.
#
EMOTE :

Show people what you're feeling.  The shorthand is ":".

"emote <string>" will display your name, then the string.  For example,
if your name is "Quifael",

> emote is feeling very sad today.

will display:

Quifael is feeling very sad today.

See also: SOCIALS, SOCIAL
#
"ENCHANT WEAPON"
Usage          : cast 'enchant weapon' <target> : cast 24 <target>
Duration       : Permanent
Cost           : 80 Mn
Effect         : +2 Hitroll, +2 Damroll to the weapon.

Also if the caster is evil, the weapon will become anti-good and if the 
caster is good, the weapon becomes anti-evil.

Enchant weapon, only works with non magical weapons. A weapon can't be
re-enchanted.
#
"ENERGY DRAIN"
Usage           : cast 'energy drain' <victim> : cast 25 <victim>
Damage          : explained below
Cost            : 20 Mn
Duration        : instant

   If the opponents level is less than 3, this spell will do 100 in 
damage, otherwise it only does 1d10 in damage.
#
ENTER

If you type 'enter' while you are outdoors, you'll enter any nearby 
shelter.  You can also follow 'enter' with an argument; for example:

>enter window

When in room presents portal, you try to enter portal, for example:

>enter moongate

#
ESCAPE

This skill is the knowledge of how to avoid panic facing overwelming 
enemies.  Instead of fleeing there is a chance that you may succed with 
your escape, loosing no experience.  It is however a difficult skill.
#
ETHICS

                      IMMORTAL CODE OF ETHICS

I.     Be fair.  This doesn't just mean to try to act fair.  It also 
       means avoiding situations in which your impartiality can be 
       compromised.  These situations can include enforcing policy where 
       clan members, friends, signifigant others or enemies are 
       concerned.  If this means waiting until another non-involved 
       immortal arrives, so be it.

       A.  Fairness is more important than justice.
       B.  If you are personally involved in a rules dispute, odds are 
           you can't be fair.  Get another immortal to adjudicate it.
       C.  Your immortal is a tool to be used to help the mud, not a 
           bonus to help your mortals or the mortals of others.  This 
           means you should avoid situations where your immortal gives 
           you an edge in zones.  If you write a zone, try to avoid 
           running it for items or experience until others get a chance.  
           If you are online, resist the urge to log on a mortal when you 
           see areas reset.

II.    Listen.  Don't assume things about mortals, and don't act like 
       they are stupid.  If they are talking to us, they have something 
       important to say.

III.   Understand.  Remember, a lot of things on a mud can make people
       angry.  Try to understand why a mortal feels the way he does.
       Put yourself in their shoes.

IV.   Be considerate.  Having an immortal gives you a lot of clout in
      discussions.  Use it, don't abuse it.  Always remember that you
      are an immortal and represent Elite, even when you are playing
      a mortal.

      A.  A special note on consideration.  Remember, many of our users
          speak english as their second language.  Be very courteous when
          dealing with these people, and try your best to understand what
          they are saying.  Sometimes this will mean asking another god 
          to help.
      B.  While there is nothing wrong with being invisible, try to be
          visible when actually punishing mortals.  If you have reason
          to be invisible, consider why;  you may have a conflict of
          interest (such as the mortal hates you) and in this case, it
          is better if you ask another immortal to help.

V.    Use common sense.  Don't get angry when dealing with mortals.  It
      only makes it worse.  If they are angry, let them blow off some
      steam first.  If you are angry, stop dealing with them problem and
      let someone else take care of it.  If people are unable to agree, 
      never underestimate the value of compromise -- even if one person
      is wrong.

VI.   Don't make a mistake because you're afraid to ask questions.  If 
      you don't know what to do, ask another immortal to help you.  Also, 
      if you need to make a ruling, be sure to gather the facts before 
      acting.  It's more important to answer the questions of "why" and 
      "how" than the question of "who", and all your rulings should have 
      a basis in fact, and not rhetoric or bias.

VII.  The immortals are a team.  The best way for us to work is through
      constructive work and constructive criticism.  If we have problems,
      they should be solved among the immortals -- including the mortals
      in our conflicts will only make them worse.

VIII. EliteMUD is a hobby for all of us, just as it is a hobby for the
      players.  All your actions should be guided by this concept;  this
      is not a job, it is a game.

#
EQUIPMENT

Gives you a list of all the equipment you're wearing, holding, and 
wielding.

See also: INVENTORY REMOVE WEAR HOLD WIELD
#
EXAMINE

May give you some valuable information about an item.

> exam girdle
will show what is in the girdle.

See also: LOOK
#
EXITS

Gives you a list of the obvious exits from your location. Of course, the 
less obvious ones won't show up here - you have to THINK in order to 
locate those.
#
EXPERIENCE XP

Whenever you kill a monster, you earn experience points. When
enough experience points are earned, you raise a level.
Things you should know about experience points:

  * When damaging a monster, you get experience points.

  * If you kill a monster of higher level than yourself, you get bonus
    experience points. If killing a monster of lower level you'll gain
    less experience points

See Also: GROUP, LEVELS, LEVEL, SCORE, STAT
#
FAIRY FAIRIES

Fairies are a magical race of woodland creatures that are believed to
be descendants of the spirits of the forest themselves.  They are tiny,
beautiful beings with gossamer wings and pointed ears.  Their hair
and eyes have the same variation in color as the forest itself.  Fairies
are weak because of their small size, but because they often live for
several hundred years they are usually very wise.  They are inherently
magical creatures, and are often protected from harm by the very forces
of nature that created them.  Fairy folk are playful and friendly, but
tend to stay close to the forests from which they come.  Fairies only
recently began to venture into Midgaard from the surrounding forests, so
not much is known about this mystical race.
#
FELINE
                             #GFELINES#N

From their treetop paradise, hidden high in the jungles to the south, 
came a race of catlike beings.  They are the chosen protectors of the 
jungle that they call home.  This leads to them being wary of the same 
strangers that had once threatened their wildlife homes.  The battles of 
good and evil are of little concern to them, they will adapt to suit 
their needs.  They are humble creatures that do not boast of power or 
strength.  Their heightened senses, great agility, and quick wit are all 
they need to survive and prosper.

                           #G REQUIREMENTS: #N

Applicants must be at least level 50 or a remort.  The quest consists of
three (3) parts and requires creative writing and roleplaying.

#
