#
MINOTAUR

Minotaurs are the descendants of a cursed beast that was half man and
half bull.  They are large and strong, but they are normally not very
intelligent.  The minotaurs that venture into Midgaard tend to get
into many fights because of their strong wills and violent natures.
Minotaurs usually have dark brown or black fur covering their heads and
backs.  They have a long tail and two sharp horns on their bull-like
heads, with the torso, legs and arms of a human.  Minotaurs have their
own code of honor: "The one still standing is the winner."  These fierce
creatures are intimidating and are often shunned by all other races due 
to their war-like nature.
#
MONK

These devout priests are the protectors of their temples. Through
meditation and relaxation, they discovered the secrets of the
martial arts.

    You can improve your spells and skills by using the practice
command in Cleric Guild.

See also: PRACTICE, GUILD, MIDGAARD
#
MORIA
The Moria Mountains is the east mountains. The rumors are that this 
mountains once where a great dwarven strong hold. Now the old caves and 
mines have been taken over by orcs and other evil creatures. The Dwarfs 
have established a new home further up the mountains.
#
"MOUNTED BATTLE"

The skill of fighting most effectively on a horse back.  Unused 
adventurers are only hampered by their horses, but you know how to use 
the mount as an advantage.
#
"MYSTICAL COAT"
Usage            : cast 'mysticial coat' : cast 75
