PIERCE

A general skill for all classes.  The knowledge of how to use piercing
weapons like spears.  You will have a greater chance of hitting your 
enemy with a piercing weapon.

See also:  BLUDGEON SLASH STAB CHOP
#
PK KILLING PLAYER_KILLING

Player Killing (PK) is completely illegal except in the PK zone.  The PK
zone is, from the market square, 3w5swse.  Once inside the zone, you
*must* obey the following rules:

* All PK is by consent only.  This means you must preplan your fights.
  Once the fight ends, you must stop fighting, and in order to fight
  again, you must once more agree to the fight.  Also, the fight only
  begins when all contestents are ready.

* You are no longer a part of any PK if you leave the zone.  This means
  dying, being summoned out, walking out, and so on.  This includes
  leaving by accident.  In short, if you leave, stop fighting.

* There is no grouping in PK.

* If you wish to make terms before the fight (such as no potions, or
  no eq, or no circling, etc), you should get an outside party such
  as an immortal to observe the fight.  This ensures that all parties
  obey the rules.  Breaking agreed-upon terms is the same thing as
  breaking official PK rules.

* Violators of these rules will be crushed.  Happy PKing!
#
POISON

Usage            : cast 'poison' <target> : cast 33 <target>
Effect           : Poison target, STR -2
Duration         : level of caster
Cost             : 16 Mn

If someone is poisoned, he or she will loose some hp instead of
gaining every hour.
#
"POISON BLADE"

Veteran rogues know the benefit of always keeping their weapons tainted 
with poison.  The poison is seldom deadly, but having the enemy 
disoriented and dizzy is always an advantage.
#
POLICY

This command provides a summary of the policies of EliteMUD ranging from
topics like playerkilling through to acceptable language on channels.

For more info on certain topics, type the following:
                #wHELP POLICY <TOPIC>#N

Choose one of the following policy numbers / topics:
        ONE          TWO          THREE        FOUR         FIVE
        SIX          SEVEN        EIGHT        NINE         REIMB
        CHANNELS     LANGUAGE     

Thanks to Mokky, Bod and Titan for source of POLICY related topics.

#
"POLICY ONE"  

EliteMUD Policy - ONE - Player Killing (PK)

No player killing.  This includes charming, cursing, blinding,
poisoning, or otherwise causing harm or trouble to other players.

There is however a PKOK zone where this rule is not applied, but
players involved must be consenting.       

Note: Players who are part of the Global PKOK system are ONLY
affected by this policy if they kill another player who is not
participating in the Global PKOK system (all participating
players are clearly identifiable and no excuses will be accepted!)

Abuse of this rule will result in severe punishment.

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  1 week frozen.#N
Second Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Deletion of offending character.#N
#
"POLICY TWO"

EliteMUD Policy - TWO - Player Theft (PT)

No stealing from other players. This includes stealing / looting
other's corpses or kills. Killing a mob in a room where another
player is already present is kill stealing, so is killing a mob 
in a room where a player is sleeping. 

Additionally you may not steal from or otherwise interfere with
mobs in a room where another player is already present.

Ask before you kill away!

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  1 day jail time.#N
Second Offense:
    #C<MAX>  7 days jail time.#N
Third+ Offense:
    #C<MAX>  4 weeks jail time.#N
#
"POLICY THREE"

EliteMUD Policy - THREE - Harassment

No harassing other players. This includes summoning and / or reciting
recalls on other players without explicit permission, spamming, and
excessive use of charmed mobs on public channels. Deliberate attempts
to trigger actions on other players' mud clients is considered
harrassment as well.

Ask if you don't understand what that means!

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  1 day jail time.#N
Second+ Offense:
    #C<MIN>  1 day jail time.#N
    #C<MAX>  Deletion / Siteban.#N
#
"POLICY FOUR"

EliteMUD Policy - FOUR - Personal Harassment

A special case of harassment is personal harassment. This includes
swearing directed at someone in tell, belittlement, sexual harassment,
and other related personal attacks. This applies to boards / postings
as well.  Libelous or hateful writings will not be tolerated.

Ask if you don't understand what that means!

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  5 days jail time.#N
Second+ Offense:
    #C<MIN>  1 week jail time.#N
    #C<MAX>  Deletion / Siteban.#N
#
"POLICY FIVE"

EliteMUD Policy - FIVE - Swearing / Language

No swearing on public channels, in titles/plans or harassing others
in any way by showing off your elementary knowledge in bad slang.
Elite is a family mud where everyone is respected.
See NOTE below.

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  24 hours mute / title ban.#N
Second+ Offense:
    #C<MIN>  24 hours mute / title ban.#N
    #C<MAX>  1 week jail.#N

However, Elite has a special channel for swearing and related bad
language. See #wHELP POLICY CHANNELS#N for more info.
#
"POLICY SIX"

EliteMUD Policy - SIX - Multi-Playing

NO MULTI-PLAYING. You may not under any circumstances have more than
one (1) character logged on, or at the menu. This is not to say that 
you may not own more than one character. It is NOT allowed to group
your multiple characters together and adventure, leave a character
behind (to heal or summon) while you adventure with the other
character, or trade of goods between characters.

AGAIN: NEVER have more than one character on at the same time. #r
It is also forbidden to leave one character linkdead and log on 
another one.#N  NO other characters anywhere in the game, not even 
at the main menu for whatever reason.

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  3 weeks jail for all characters involved.#N
Second Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Deletion of all offending characters.#N
#
"POLICY SEVEN"

EliteMUD Policy - SEVEN - Bug Abuse  

REPORT BUGS.  You must report any bug you find in the game.
Using a bug to your advantage, or using commands in a way that they 
clearly were not intended for is a serious abuse.
        #C
The Maximum penalty for such offenses includes a total siteban.#N
#
"POLICY EIGHT"

EliteMUD Policy - EIGHT - Unattended Processes / AFK Botting or Camping

Most unattended processes are banned. Unattended processes are things
your mud client does automatically without you being at the keyboard.
Eating / drinking and giving spells to yourself is the only exception.
While you are afk, you can only use these triggers in clan houses or 
in Midgaard. Running zones, botting, and anything else you can automate
are okay if you're sitting at the keyboard. When you leave, you must
disable these. The penalties are the same as for multiplaying.

Additionally anything else you can think of while AFK (through the use
of a client or other means) is subject to the same punishment.

First Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Forced to read Policy and given a warning.#N
    #C<MAX>  3 weeks jail for all characters involved.#N
Second Offense:
    #C<MIN>  Deletion of all offending characters.#N
#
"POLICY NINE"

EliteMUD Policy - NINE - Password Sharing / Trading Characters

Password sharing between players is also illegal.  If you are found
sharing passwords with another player, or hacking other players'
characters you will be punished.

This also means that it is illegal to trade characters between players.
        #C
The Maximum penalty for such offenses includes a total siteban.#N
#
"POLICY CHANNELS"

EliteMUD Policy - CHANNELS - Correct usage of Public Channels

There are a lot of different communication channels available for
different purposes and it should not be that difficult to follow
them.  No advertising other muds on any channel, folks.

1. #CGRAT#N channel:   This is the ONLY channel where messages
   regarding level gains and congratulations thereof belong. Keep
   those here.

2. #GCHAT#N channel:   This is a communications channel meant for
   mud-related topics that may be of interest to the entire mud.

3. #YGOSSIP#N channel:   This is a general communication channel,
   it is meant for funny, serious, or any other kind of messages that
   are not mud-related.  This is also the only channel where you can
   use your colourful language and swear, as long as you are not
   harassing any other player.

4. #RYELL#N channel:   Yell sends your message to everyone in the same
   zone as you.

5. #mQUEST#N channel:   This channel exists solely for information
   to be exchanged during quests, and should be turned off when
   quest is over. It should go without saying, anything talked about
   on it should be quest related.

6. #wNEWBIE#N channel:   This channel is for newer players to request
   help, and for more experienced players to assist them.

7. #MAUCTION#N channel:   This is a communications channel meant for
   the selling, bidding and purchase of items.

8. #rPK-SAY#N channel:   This is a communications channel meant for
   PK-related topics that may be of interest.
        #r
Please note the the only channel where any language other than ENGLISH
is acceptable is #YGOSSIP#r!#N
#
"POLICY LANGUAGE"

EliteMUD Policy - LANGUAGE - Acceptable Language Guidelines

With the exception of the gossip channel, swearing on public channels
should be only mild at worst. This is the type of language that you
might hear in a PG rated film.

This mud has always had a policy of keeping all public channels except
gossip as "family rated". There is absolutely no way to "prescribe" what
what can and cannot be said - at least we couldn't think of a way. So we 
checked out the BBFC (British Board of Film Classification) to see how 
-they- decide what is acceptable:
    #C
Many people are offended, some of them deeply, by bad language, including
the use of expletives with a religious association. The extent of that
offence varies according to age, background and beliefs. Different groups
(for example, a minority ethnic community) have their own, seperate
standards of acceptability. Additionally, the severity of any particular
word or expression will depend upon the context within which it is used.

For these reasons, it is impossible to set out comprehensive list of
acceptable words or expressions which will satisfy all sections of the
public. The advice at different classification levels, therefore, provides
general guidance with reference to specific terms only where there is a
reasonable consensus of opinion.#N

So, there you have it....THEY cant decide either. They use their judgement,
and offer the following guidelines. They suggest swearing be classified in
the following broad bands: #wHELP POLICY CLASSIFICATION#N
#
"POLICY CLASSIFICATION"

EliteMUD Policy - CLASSIFICATION - Language Classification 

The BBFC (British Board of Film Classification) suggest swearing be 
classified in the following broad bands:
   #Y
 Very Mild#N:  Damn, Hell, god, bloody, son-of-a-bitch, sod, tart, crap#Y
      Mild#N:  Bugger, screw, arse, slag, slut, tosser, Jesus Christ, 
             dickhead, bitch, shit#Y
  Moderate#N:  Piss off, whore, arsehole, prick, bollocks, twat, bastard, 
             wanker, shag#Y
    Strong#N:  Fuck#Y
Very Strong#N: Motherfucker, cunt


To be honest, we were a little surprised at some of the words rated as 
"moderate" (they were strong when Mokky was a regular user). Regardless 
we think they are a pretty good basis for determining acceptable language.

Aside from gossip, swearing should be kept at #RMILD#N or less (which is  
equivalent to that heard in a PG film). We are sorry that we can't put 
that in context for those of you from countries other than the UK.

Those words which constitute #MModerate#N swearing, should result in a polite  
request to move the conversation to gossip. Stronger language may or may  
not warrant a warning depending on context, and depending on whether the 
player is a newbie, or if they have perhaps used chat instead of ct by   
mistake. #rIn all cases, if the swearing is blatant or persistent, punishment 
will be forthcoming.#N
#
"POLICY REIMB"

EliteMUD Policy - REIMB - Reimbursement

These rules are not set in stone, but in general they will be followed.

  i) Money and experience will not be reimbursed.  Use of the Elite's
     ATM system will prevent major money loss, and Elite's periodic
     saving of the player file will prevent major loss of experience.

 ii) In general, only equipment that was in use will be reimbursed.

iii) Eq gained in a multiple crash situation will not be reimbed:
        "The Mud giveth and the Mud taketh away".

 iv) The reimbursement of quest or special eq, being that it is rare
     in nature may need to be approved by a 115 Immortal or the Quest
     group leader.

  v) The mud has a sweeper. It will clean up any item on the ground
     every time a zone resets. Only clan houses and Godrooms are 
     immune to this. One other room immune to this is the Midgaard
     Chat Room (ws of Temple). If items are lost due to the sweeper
     they will NOT be reimbursed.

 vi) There is a 100 item limit on what you may have on your character.
     If you go over this limit and lose items due to logging out or a
     mud crash, it will not be reimbursed. 
