RACE

There are are twenty five different races available on Elite. Most are 
available to starting players and remorts. These are:

human          elf          half-elf       dwarf         gnome
halfling       fairy        minotaur       ratman        drow
lizard         troll        draconian

As a 4th remort, you may choose to become an Avatar race.

There are also six quest races which are available. See the quest board
for further details of how to become one of these:

werewolf      dragon     demon      feline      angel     vampire



#
RANGER

Rangers dwell in the forest. They are masters of the bow, and have great
skill in hunting. Through their time spent in the forest, they have
acquired some minor forest magics.

    You can improve your spells and skills by using the practice
command in Warrior Guild.

See also: PRACTICE, GUILD, MIDGAARD
#
RATMAN

Ratmen are the creation of a cruel god that made common sewer rats larger
and smarter.  Though they are infinitely more intelligent than their
primitive ancestors, ratmen are still prone to rummaging through garbage.
They are usually covered with thick brown or black fur and have beady
black eyes and a large pink tail.  Some ratmen have white hair and pink
eyes, but this rare breed is nearly extinct due to their participation in
extensive experimentation done by local alchemists.  Ratmen are cunning
and sly, and very capable of complex reasoning, but they tend to prefer
trades that allow them to live off of the prosperity of others.
#
READ

When you want to read something.
#
RECALL

Until level 10 you can type RECALL if you wish to be transfered back to
temple. This is very useful if you get lost etc and it will not cost
you anything. After level 10 you can buy scrolls of recall in the
Wizards shop in Midgaard.

See Also: MIDGAARD, RECITE, SCROLL
#
RECITE SCROLL SCROLLS

Use : Recite <Scroll> [Target]

Is used to "read" a magical scroll. Target can be an object, character or
nothing (which may be yourself).

See Also: RECALL
#
REDRAW

If you have display vt ot ansi on, and the screen gets messed up for 
various of reasons, use redraw to correct that.  No parameters needed.

See also DISPLAY RESIZE
#
"REGENERATION"
Usage          : cast 'regeneration' <victim> : cast 61 <victim>
Effect         : Increases regen
Cost           : 60 Mn
Duration       : 7 hours

When cast, this spell will speed up a player's metabolsm, causing
an increased health sensation. The effect will cause you to regenerate
hit points much faster then normal.
#
REMORT

A remort is a mortal character, that is, in most cases, more powerful
than your average mortal.  Being a remort allows you to choose any
class combination you want, assuming you follow the simply rules.
The main benefit is that you are now able to make class combinations
that are not available to you when you make a new character.
There are no exceptions, and all remorts will be done according to
the rules as they are posted here.  Any questions that you might have
may be directed at a member of the Remort Team.

For more info on certain topics, type the following:
                HELP REMORT <TOPIC>

Choose one of the following topics:
        READY         CLASS      SECOND         FOURTH
        RACE          FIRST      THIRD          TRI

Thanks to Phobos, Phish and Fitzroy for source of REMORT related topics.

#
"REMORT READY"

Here are some questions to ask yourself before you ask to be
remorted. Doing this will save you some time in the Remort Lab.

* Are you 109 in all of your classes?  If not, go level.

* Is all of your gold in the bank?  If not, put it in or you will
lose it upon remorting.

* Are you carrying any objects?  If you are, be sure that they are
usable by a level 1 character.  If they are not, you must either put
them in a locker or give them to another character.  If they are,
you may keep them with you while being remorted.  Just as a reminder,
you will be asked to remove and drop everything you have on you.

* For first remorts, do you know which race you want to be?  If not,
you should make a decision.

* Do you know what class you want to be, and are you sure that you
are allowed to be that class?

#
"REMORT RACE"
On your first remort, you must select a race.  You may choose any
race you want, except for god, avatar, dragon, demon, werewolf,
feline, or vampire.  The ONLY way you can be one of these races is
if you already are one before you remort.

After you select your race for your first remort, you are stuck
with that race until you reach your fourth remort.  Choose wisely,
there will be no leniency in changing races after they have been
set to you.

On your fourth remort, you can become an avatar if you wish.  You
get all of your stats maxed to 23.  Naturally, if you do not want
to be an avatar, you do not have to be.  For example, if you are a
dragon, you are free to keep dragon as your race if you wish.  You
would still get your stats maxed in any case.

#
"REMORT CLASS"
There are four basic archtypes, warrior, cleric, thief and
magic user.  Each of these archtypes are the base for three
special classes.  If you type 'help class' you will see a
list of all of the classes offered on Elite.

The archtype classes are listed in the first column.  The
special classes associated with each archtype are in the
same row as the archtype they are based on.  For example,
the special types that are derrived from a warrior are
knight, ranger, and cavalier.

See also CLASS

#
"REMORT FIRST"

Anyone who is level 109 in all of their classes and is not a
remort may ask to become a first remort.  When you become a
first remort, you are put back at level one, with new classes
and a new race and start all over again.

Your race choices are outlined in the post marked RACES.  The
way your class choice works is this:   First, you pick whatever
class you are now.  If you are a multi-class, you must pick one
of your classes.  If the class that you have chosen is a special
class (ie, anything but a wa/th/cl/mu), you downgrade it to it's
archtype (Kn -> Wa, Mo -> Cl, etc...).  Next, you add another
archtype, and are now a dual class character.  Then, you pick one
of your two classes and upgrade it to a special class.

For example:  John the 109 th/cl picks cleric as his class.  Then
he adds warrior to it.  This now makes him a wa/cl.  He upgrades
the warrior to a ranger and John becomes a level 1, Ra/Cl.  This
seems fairly simple, if there are any questions, ask a remort god.

#
"REMORT SECOND"

In order to become a second remort, you must be a first remort that
is level 109 in all of your classes.  However, the rules now change
a little bit.

You may not pick a new race.  As you were told when you remorted for
the first time, you are stuck with that race until your fourth remort.

This time around, instead of picking one of your classes going through
the procedure for a first remort, you simply upgrade your remaining
archtype to a special type.

For example.  John, our level 109/109 Ra/Cl wishes to second remort.
He chooses druid as his second class.  He then becomes John, the
level 1 Ra/Dr.  And off to level he goes.

#
"REMORT THIRD"

To become a third remort, you must be a second remort who is level
109 in all of your classes.  Again, the rules are slightly
different from those of previous remorts.

This time around, you keep the two archtypes that you have from
your second remort, and add a third class.  You may add any of the
four archtypes.  As with second remorts, you are not allowed to
change your race.

For example, John, our level 109/109 Ra/Dr wants to third remort.
He chooses to add thief as a new class, and he then becomes
John, the level 1 Ra/Dr/Th.

#
"REMORT FOURTH"

In order to become a fourth remort, you must be a third remort
who is level 109 in all of your classes.  Unlike previous
remorts, you have a few more options this time around.

Race -- You may choose to become an avatar this time around.
Avatars are the best race that is still available to mortals.
If you do not want to be an avatar, that is your choice.  If
you are a quest race, you may keep that race.  If you are not
a quest race, and do not wish to become an avatar, you may pick
any other race you wish.

Hunger & Thirst --  You have the option of having hunger and
thirst toggled off.  If you do not want hunger and thirst off,
it is your responsibility to say so.  Vampires may not have
their blood turned off, being that they are required to role
play the vampire to remain powerful.

Maxed Stats -- No matter what race you choose on your fourth
remort, you are allowed to have your stats maxed if you wish.
If for some reason you do not want your stats maxed, it is your
responsibility to say so.

Class -- You may pick any class combination on your fourth
remort, be it a single, dual, or tri class structure.  You are
not limited to your previous classes in any way.

For example, John, our level 109/109/109 Ra/Dr/Th wants to
fourth remort.  He decides to become an avatar race and wants
to be a Ca/Wi/Cl.  However silly this may seem it is a valid
choice and he then becomes John, the level 1 Ca/Wi/Cl.  He
gets all of his stats maxed and his hunger and thirst toggled
off.

Note:  You will be charged 10M gold for each time you remort
       after your 4th.  

#
"REMORT TRI"

Because of the TRI clan, we have a special set of rules for people
who desire to remain TRI class characters for all of their remorts.

First Remort:  Instead of the rules stated, he keeps his three
classes (wa/cl/mu or wa/th/mu) and is allowed to change any one of
them to a special class.

Second Remort:  Instead of the rules stated, he keeps his first
remort race, and has the OPTION to change one of his archtypes to
any other archtype.  Sorry, Your special class has to remain the
same.

Third Remort:  Instead of the rules stated, he keeps his second
remort class and upgrades one of his archtypes to a special class.

Fourth Remort:  You may choose any class combination that you wish.

All of the rules that do not pertain to class selection are the
same for TRI remorts as with all others, ie, races, hunger/thirst,
maxing stats...

#
"REMOVE CURSE"

Usage          : cast 'remove curse' <victim> : cast 35 <victim>
Duration       : Instant
Effect         : Removes the Effect of the Curse spell on players
Cost           : 14 Mn
