"REMOVE EQUIPMENT"
If you tire of wearing some armor or wielding a weapon.

> remove boots
> remove sword
> remove all
> remove all.bronze

See also: WEAR EQUIPMENT LOCKER
#
"REMOVE POISON"
Usage         : cast 'remove poison' <victim> : cast 43 <victim>
Cost          : 14 Mn
Effect        : Removes the effects of being poisoned.
#
REPEAT

TOGGLE REPEAT toggles whether or not you see your communication echoed
back to you (i.e., from commands such as SAY, SHOUT, HOLLER, GOSSIP, 
etc.)  Useful if you have a slow connection or if it just annoys you.
#
REPLY

Reply sends a tell to the last person to tell you something. This will 
work even if the one you reply to has toggled tell of.

See Also: TELL, NOTELL
#
RESCUE

This command is useful if you want to try and make an attacker hit you
instead of your poor friend who is being pummeled.  You can only 'turn'
one monster for each rescue attempt.  This is highly useful when playing
in groups, of course.

rescue <victim>

> rescue quifael

See Also: Protect
#
RESIZE

This will resize your active window, parameters are any number from 1 to
99, the max # of lines you can have displayed on your screen.
Most standard size screens should be sized to 25 lines.

Usage: res 25 (for example)

See also DISPLAY REDRAW
#
"RIMEFANG"
Usage           : cast 'rimefang' <victim> : cast 87 <victim>
Damage          : (5d6 + 10) * (level / 6) (max of level 90)
Cost            : 40 Mn
Duration        : instantaneous
#
RIVER
The Midgaard river flows from deep within the moria mountains to the
sea. To travel on this river you need a boat, it can be bought from the
captain at the leeve in Midgaard.
#
SACRIFICE

Use SAC instead of DROP if you want to keep the world a little cleaner.  
If you SAC something, it will disappear and you'll get a few coins, just 
as if you had dropped it in the dump.

> sac cup
> sac all.bronze
> sac 500 coins

See also: DROP DONATE
#
"SANCTUARY"

Usage            : cast 'sanctuary' <victim> : cast 36 <victim>
Effect:          : Reduces the damage done to you by enemies
Cost             : 50 Mn
Duration         : 4 hours

While affected by sanctuary, you will only take half the
damage you usually would.
#
SAVE

Save your persona.  This includes experience points, strength, gold, etc.
Your equipment is also saved in the (unlikely?) event of a crash.  The
game periodically auto-saves you and your equipment, so it is not 
necessary to have your client auto-save you as well.  Aliases are saved 
as well.

You CANNOT load a saved version if you die -- your persona still exists,
but you will lose experience, and all your objects stay in the game, with
your corpse.

Note that the QUIT commands automatically saves you.  When you want to 
quit, just type quit.

#
SAY TELL ASK WHISPER YELL  '
If you consider communicating with other beings, you might be understood
better if you start your sentences with either say, tell, or whisper.

<say | yell> <string>
<tell | whisper | ask> <player> <string>

> say Hey, does anyone know how to get to Oz?
> tell uncle hi, how are you?

You can use ' as a shorthand for say, as in: ' hello there.

Yell broadcasts to everybody in your geographical zone.

Say and tell without parameters shows 10 previous messages
you heard by this way.

>say
[IO]  Hi
[Player]  Hello IO
[Newbie]  Where i can level?
[Player]  In newbie zoo.
[Remort]  Hey Player... wanna PK?
[Player]  Nope, thank IO.
[IO]  You are welcome. :)

See also: GOSSIP AUCTION GTELL NOREPEAT QSAY NOTELL REPLY DEAF
#
SCORE

Whenever you want to check whether you're still alive and healthy
or simply want to see how much money you have left.

See also: STAT
#
SCOUT

This skill will display location of mobs in your surrounding area. It's
accuracy depends on how good you are at the skill.

Example: > scout
         North: 1 - [2] Beastly Fido
         South: 2 - Mercenary

means that there are 2 beastly fidos 1 step north and 1 Mercenary 2 steps
south.

See also: TRACK
#
SCREENMODES

If your terminal supports vt100+ codes you may want to use this.  That 
will give you a info-bar in the game.  If you have a color monitor and 
can use ANSI color, this is also supported by Elite.

See Also: DISPLAY, COLOR, TOGGLE, PC
#
SECOND THIRD FOURTH ATTACK

Depending on your class, you can attack up to four times each 'round'.
All classes can practice second attack.  Only warriors, rangers, knights,
cavaliers and mariners may attack up to four times a round.

See also:  DUAL WEAPONS
