#
TITLE

Sets the title people see on the WHO list and when you're in the room 
with them.  You can't use parentheses (the "(" and ")" characters) 
because those are reserved for flags.  TITLE without any argument will 
set you title to one of the predefined.  Do not abuse this command; if 
you do, it will be taken from you.

See also:  FLAGS
#
TOGGLE

TOGGLE shows you the current values of various toggles available on the 
MUD.  This command is also used to change most of these values.
All of these toggles remain the same until you change them; i.e. they are
saved when you quit or rent.
To get a list of the things you can change, type: TOGGLE HELP

See Also:  DISPLAY BRIEF COMPACT QUEST REPEAT WIMP
#
TRACK

Used for finding the first step on the shortest route to a monster.

> track fido
#
TROLL

Trolls are ugly, strong, and dumb.  They love to fight with almost
anything that moves, and even things that don't move!  Trolls have been
known to attack even a dead foe.  Their stout bodies can take a lot
of abuse with little wear and tear, and it sure is hard for them to get
any uglier.  Trolls vary in appearance, but most tend to have dark hair
and eyes with putrid skin and teeth.  They don't normally smell very
good, a result of their taste for raw flesh.  Trolls are not the smartest
creatures, but they sure know how to fight.
#
TUMBLE

A thief skill like dodge.
