#
USE WAND STAFF STAFFS WANDS

Use : Use <Staff>
      Use <Wand> <Target>

Using staff's will automatically target everybody (or everything) in a
room, execpt yourself. Therefore staff's are naturally very powerful, and
yet may be very dangerous to use around other players.

Using wands require that you point it at a target, which can be eihter a
character or an object.

Both staff's and wand's must be HELD in the hand prior to use! (Use the
grab or hold commands). You must still supply the name of the staff or
wand to avoid confusion.

See Also: SCROLL, POTION
#
VAMPIRE
                             #mVAMPIRE#W

When a human's mortal blood is tainted by that of the undead, a vampire 
is born. These abominations of nature have the potential to be more 
powerful in every respect than a human ever could possibly imagine.  A 
vampire can incorporate the characteristics of a bat into thier bodies 
and take flight.  Also, these defilers of God's life cycle no longer 
require normal sustinance; instead they feed on the blood of their 
victims.  This act causes thier strength to grow, but the longer they 
roam without feeding the weaker they become, ensuring that their hunger 
rules their unlives eternally.

 #mTo Apply#W

The level minimum for joining the vampire quest race is 50, or remort
status.  Your writing ability, role playing talent, and mud knowledge 
will be tested.
#
