#
WEREWOLF

When the full moon rises, the werewolves prowl the streets of Midgaard.
Proud warriors able to assume the form of the wolf, these deadly 
predators battle between their own inner rage and a world that calls them 
monsters.

Defenders of nature from mankind, these creatures are known for their
inherent goodness.  Despite this, some are consumed by their rage and 
turn to evil.  These deadly beings are feared the most of all.

Contrary to mythology, werewolves are born, not made, and no-one knows
they are a were until the changes begin to occur.  Certainly, some people
may feel out of place or different from others;  they tend to be broody
and solitary, but it's not until their first rage takes them that they
know the truth.  This is often the hardest time for the new werewolf, for
they must reconcile their new, dangerous selves with their lives. 

Werewolves are the creatures born to prey on mortal men.  For this 
reason, they are dangerous, and driven by their hunger.

Chani is currently in charge of the werewolf race.
#
WHERE
Tells you which players are currently in the same zone as you.

Immortals may type 'where' without arguments to see where everybody is.

> where
#
WHO

Lists the people currently in the game.  Some people may be invisible.
Command-line options can be used to limit the listing.  The parameters
can be specified on the command-line in any order.

who [minlev[-maxlev]][-n sname][-c class][-r race][-k clanvnum]
    [-s -o -p -q -r -z -R -< ->]

minlev, maxlev : list only people whose level is at or above minlev, and
                 optionally, at or below maxlev
-< : Sort the list in ascending levels.
-> : Sort the list in descending levels.
-n : list only people whose names or titles contain sname
-c : list only people of a certain class, where class is the name of the 
     class consisting of at least 4 characters.
-r : list only people of a certain race, where race is the name of the 
     race consisting of at least 4 characters
-k : list only people of a certain clan, where clanvnum is number of the
     clan (as shown on clan info)
-s : list names in the short form.
-o : list only outlaws (i.e. people with a killer or thief flag)
-p : list only #rPKOK#N (i.e. people in the Global PK System)
-q : list only people who are on the Quest
-R : list only people who are in your room
-z : list only people in your zone

> who -c warr -s -l 20
   List, in short form, warriors and clerics at or above level 20
> who 15-25 -o -z -r duck
   List all duck outlaws between levels 15 and 25 who are in your zone.
#
WIELD

When you get tired of bashing monsters with your fists, you might 
consider wielding a weapon.

> wield sword

See also: EQUIPMENT, REMOVE EQUIPMENT, WEAR, HOLD
#
WIMP WIMPY

Use the WIMP command to automatically wimp out of a fight.

WIMP 35 will make your character automatically flee a fight if he/she has
     less than 35 hit points.
WIMP 0  will turn off wimpy mode.
WIMP    will show you your current wimp status.

See also:  TOGGLE
#
WIZARD

These spellcasters seek out ways to bind the raw energy of their
external world and harness it for their own purposes. Knowing at first
only a few megre spells, apprentice wizards can begin to learn ways to
harness the very elements of the universe.

    You can improve your spells and skills by using the practice
command in Magic Guild.

See also: PRACTICE, GUILD, MIDGAARD
#
WIZLIST IMMLIST

Immlist lists the Immortal Structure (ie who is working on what).
The structure is made up as follows:

                      Implemetor(s)
                            |
                ------------------------
               |            |           |
            Balance       Devel       World


Balance, Code and World Groups are further divided into teams.
These teams can be identified by the following colourisation: #c
Character      #YRahl #NKosomot

and the Team Head (as per above example) is displayed in #Yyellow#N.

Some of these teams contain sub-teams and these are displayed
in #Ccyan#N. ie#c
Information    #YArticus#C
Helpfiles                             Imm Training   #NTurf



Wizlist lists the Immortals in the more formal level structure.
It does not list retired or trainee immortals (110-111)
#
WIZNAME PRENAME
Format of player information as it shows up on the "who" list:

[Wizname] Prename <player-name> title [clan title]

  #yPrenames#N are given if you are level 100 or above.
  Non-standard #rWiznames#N are given if you are a 3rd remort or higher.

To set a WIZNAME or PRENAME type "wizname <text>" or "prename <text>"

See also: REMORT

#
"WORD OF HEALING"
Usage            : cast 'word of healing' <target> : cast  50 <target>
Effect           : 2d8
Cost             : 6 Mn
Duration         : Instant

A healing spell.
#
"WORD OF RECALL"
Usage          : cast 'word of recall' : cast 42
Effect         : Teleports to safety
Cost           : 30 Mn
Duration       : Instant

When cast, this spell will safely transport the caster to the temple
of Midgaard. Only possible to use on yourself.
#
WORSHIP

The worship system work like this:

   After a certain level (5) you can start worshipping any player
above a certain level (99).  You do this with WORSHIP PLAYERNAME.

> worship <player>

Note that you cannot abbreviate the worship command.  If you do it'll be
considered as the worship social. (worshi)  Worship will give your deity 
or hero more power, thereby showing how popular he/she/it is.  The person 
will naturally be more helpful towards their worshippers.

Also note that only long term worshipping, ie not change deities often, 
will affect the worshipped.  Sporadically changing deity does nothing.  
There is also a PENALTY for changing deities.  You LOSE all your current 
EXPERIENCE.  This do not apply when you first start to worship someone.  

You can check whom you are worshipping in the SCORE list.
#
WRITE

In order to write a note, you need a piece of blank paper (or similar), 
and a pen of some sort. You can then type something like "write on the 
paper with the pen", whereupon you'll be asked to type in your note at 
the keyboard.

To post a message on a board:
> write <headline>

See Also: BOARD
#~

